WEBVTT

00:00.482 --> 00:03.487
Welcome to our Wednesday services.

00:03.507 --> 00:06.151
We're celebrating the season of Lent here together.

00:06.892 --> 00:10.537
If this is your first time coming tonight, we welcome you.

00:11.138 --> 00:18.469
We don't normally meet every Wednesday like this, but during the season of Lent, we, you know, it's all about inconveniencing ourselves.

00:20.532 --> 00:26.241
And so we volunteer some reason to come out here on Wednesday nights, but it's neat.

00:26.261 --> 00:27.082
I love this idea.

00:27.102 --> 00:29.746
I don't know if you're joining with some of us who are

00:29.826 --> 00:33.611
fasting for the day, and then we get to break the fast with the soup afterwards.

00:33.712 --> 00:37.157
So as that smell hits me, you'll notice I preach faster.

00:38.438 --> 00:40.041
So we can get on to that.

00:40.481 --> 00:41.242
But it's neat.

00:41.423 --> 00:44.807
So much of our faith is just private.

00:45.268 --> 00:46.570
It's ourself.

00:46.830 --> 00:57.746
We spend time just privately praying and privately reading our scriptures and even normally coming into a church, a big church like this, it's easy just to sit there and just kind of you sit by yourself.

00:57.922 --> 01:06.354
On these Wednesdays, it sort of pushes us out of that and then makes our faith a little more public and social, which is a good thing, amen?

01:07.156 --> 01:08.818
So thank you very much for being here.

01:09.920 --> 01:16.890
Tonight, so I'm gonna do just kind of a short in a message and then we'll break bed together afterwards with some soup.

01:17.531 --> 01:27.826
And what I'm gonna be doing tonight is just kind of talking about this idea of sort of setting it up and kind of explaining again, maybe you've heard us say it over and over again, but I'll say it a little differently.

01:27.906 --> 01:32.232
about Lent and why we're doing this and why we're gathering together over this season.

01:33.755 --> 01:39.183
This season of Lent, it's a, I love this in a weird way.

01:39.804 --> 01:41.606
It's kind of a season you can both love and hate.

01:42.568 --> 01:49.798
But I love getting together like this and sort of taking time in the season and messing with ourselves.

01:49.858 --> 01:55.026
And it can be tough because we try to cram more stuff in our already busy schedule.

01:55.394 --> 02:04.083
You know, like I said, it's already tough to find room to do things in your life and then we choose to come out again on another night of the week.

02:04.123 --> 02:04.903
We were just at church.

02:04.923 --> 02:05.724
Well, you got to be there again.

02:05.784 --> 02:08.647
And maybe some questions you heard from your children.

02:09.368 --> 02:12.170
And it also messes with us.

02:12.311 --> 02:18.917
We kind of get annoyed in our day because maybe you're giving up something for Lent and it's, you know, if it's chocolate or this.

02:18.937 --> 02:23.922
I'm not a chocolate guy, but if you're into that kind of thing, you know, that time where it hits you and you just,

02:24.450 --> 02:25.811
You know, you yearn for it.

02:25.991 --> 02:28.994
And it's like as soon as you say you're not going to have it, right?

02:29.135 --> 02:32.818
It's like there's nothing more in the world that that's what I want.

02:32.838 --> 02:34.860
I don't know if it's this rebellious thing inside us.

02:34.900 --> 02:36.482
Tell me I can't have chocolate.

02:36.502 --> 02:38.203
And that's all you see is chocolate.

02:38.223 --> 02:41.927
And then at some point you're convincing yourself, maybe the Lord's telling me I should have chocolate.

02:42.007 --> 02:42.528
I don't know.

02:42.548 --> 02:46.191
I just, you make time for prayer and do all of those things.

02:46.211 --> 02:47.512
But it's good to mess with us.

02:47.693 --> 02:53.298
You know, it's kind of like holding up a mirror to our soul to see what's going on in there.

02:53.762 --> 03:01.873
2 Corinthians, chapter 13, Paul writes that we are to examine ourselves, to see whether we are in the faith, to test ourselves.

03:02.794 --> 03:06.119
And we examine ourselves by engaging in these things that mess with us.

03:07.080 --> 03:10.244
They take us out of our comfort zones and they cause us to react.

03:11.446 --> 03:15.151
You can learn a lot about yourself by seeing how you react to things.

03:17.354 --> 03:20.338
It reminds me of my dad's

03:20.738 --> 03:24.366
radio show, he used to do the Mark Gungar show, he had to retire from that, so it was driving him crazy.

03:24.928 --> 03:27.614
But he would get the same questions over and over again.

03:27.955 --> 03:33.167
And I remember he had this saying, it was when people would write in about who they're dating and things of that nature.

03:33.207 --> 03:36.916
He said, you know, you date the act and you marry the react.

03:38.078 --> 03:39.602
And the idea behind this was is

03:39.810 --> 03:44.878
He would get in these emails and it'd be some lovely lady and she'd be like, oh, my boyfriend.

03:44.898 --> 03:47.923
He's so sweet and he's so kind and he's so wonderful to me.

03:47.943 --> 03:48.924
He just cares for me so much.

03:49.365 --> 03:51.929
You know, sometimes when he gets mad, he takes the dog and kicks it across the room.

03:54.393 --> 03:57.938
And his car broke down and he just cursed like crazy and was hammered there.

03:57.958 --> 04:00.061
But he's a good guy, but he really loves me.

04:00.081 --> 04:01.884
And I just want to know.

04:02.405 --> 04:05.650
You see, all those nice things you're seeing, that's the act.

04:06.722 --> 04:07.463
He's dating, right?

04:07.924 --> 04:09.987
When you're dating someone, that's like the job interview.

04:10.067 --> 04:11.269
You're on your best behavior.

04:11.329 --> 04:13.832
You embellish your resume, the whole thing.

04:15.735 --> 04:18.139
But when you get married, oh, you marry that react.

04:18.379 --> 04:19.921
This is why it's good if you are dating.

04:19.941 --> 04:25.349
Get your boyfriend or girlfriend in situations that mess with them a little bit just to see how they react.

04:26.110 --> 04:27.212
Because that's who you're going to marry.

04:27.572 --> 04:31.538
And that's what happens to us in the season.

04:31.714 --> 04:37.142
Find time for extra prayer, which is so hard, because it's like I've never been more tired in my life than when I want to kick into extra prayer.

04:38.304 --> 04:38.625
Fast.

04:40.187 --> 04:40.508
Thank you.

04:40.628 --> 04:41.789
Love you too.

04:41.810 --> 04:45.115
Fasting, of course, will mess with us as well, right?

04:45.275 --> 04:49.081
Because it's like when you don't want things just those, you know, you begin to manifest inside.

04:49.922 --> 04:54.309
Gatherings like this can mess with us, all the work to get everyone out the door again for another week.

04:55.050 --> 05:00.338
But it's in those moments that we find worthy as my uncle,

05:00.706 --> 05:04.511
what I always tell me when I was learning about Lent, he said, that's where the dragons lie.

05:05.773 --> 05:07.014
And he told the story.

05:07.034 --> 05:14.264
He said, you know, back when they were making maps, the map makers, they would write out everything that they knew, right?

05:14.584 --> 05:19.311
They knew that the mountain was here, they'd write the mountain, they knew the river was here, they knew, and they'd write where everything was.

05:19.331 --> 05:24.818
But in the areas that were not explored and they didn't know what was there, they would just write where the dragons lie.

05:25.474 --> 05:27.076
It's the unexamined area.

05:27.096 --> 05:33.583
And that's what happens when you fast, you take things out of your life, or you mess with yourself like that, we sort of find where those dragons lie.

05:33.623 --> 05:39.230
It's kind of like doing a stress test, right, on ourselves.

05:39.850 --> 05:42.353
Kind of see how we're doing.

05:42.373 --> 05:44.736
And the truth is, we all think we're doing great.

05:45.817 --> 05:46.858
You know, we do.

05:47.299 --> 05:48.160
If you ask, how are you doing spiritually?

05:48.180 --> 05:48.700
I'm doing real good.

05:49.001 --> 05:49.321
I'm good.

05:49.782 --> 05:50.262
Love them, God.

05:50.362 --> 05:50.723
Doing great.

05:50.743 --> 05:51.483
I treat people nicely.

05:52.264 --> 05:53.746
Well, yeah, that's because we have a stress test, yeah.

05:54.626 --> 06:00.612
It's kind of like you get a group of guys my age and their forties together and you talk about like working out or something.

06:00.632 --> 06:01.593
How many pull-ups do you think you can do?

06:01.793 --> 06:03.776
We all base it off of what we did 20 years ago.

06:05.517 --> 06:06.879
Right, guys?

06:06.899 --> 06:08.340
Maybe we could do 15 back then.

06:08.400 --> 06:09.842
We'll say, well, maybe I could do eight now.

06:10.763 --> 06:13.005
Then you get up there and you actually do it and you realize you could barely get two.

06:14.587 --> 06:15.207
Oh, why?

06:15.488 --> 06:17.710
Well, because it's one thing for us to think what we can do.

06:18.431 --> 06:19.132
I still got it.

06:20.673 --> 06:21.554
I can still run a...

06:21.826 --> 06:23.368
Sub six minute miles straight.

06:23.388 --> 06:26.292
No, man, you're gonna pass out a heart attack, like a quarter mile down the road.

06:27.733 --> 06:35.043
But what happens here is when we put ourselves into a pressure situation, we sort of see if we're operating within our specs, right?

06:35.303 --> 06:36.605
If you really think you're doing great.

06:37.245 --> 06:38.908
Because I think I'm doing pretty good.

06:38.928 --> 06:39.729
I think I love God.

06:39.889 --> 06:42.132
Okay, well, it's messed with you and kind of see what happens.

06:42.172 --> 06:44.755
And you might find areas that go, you know?

06:45.135 --> 06:48.219
For this reason alone, in Lent, it can be a little unnerving.

06:49.521 --> 06:50.322
I mean, there should be a little,

06:50.882 --> 06:51.964
A little part of you that hates it.

06:53.486 --> 06:55.830
Or not, that's just me as well, as parts of it they don't love.

06:56.791 --> 07:01.398
Maybe you've already been messed with in this last week, just because you've been given up something or making more room.

07:01.418 --> 07:03.862
But now, let me make this point clear.

07:05.585 --> 07:07.147
Lent is not something that you have to do.

07:08.429 --> 07:09.931
Joining with us, it's not a requirement.

07:10.552 --> 07:14.298
There's nowhere in this scriptures that you read through that says you need to join together with Celebration Church in Lent.

07:15.159 --> 07:15.840
It does not exist.

07:16.281 --> 07:16.642
And guess what?

07:16.662 --> 07:19.506
God is not going to love you any less.

07:19.682 --> 07:21.024
if you choose not to join with it.

07:21.184 --> 07:22.065
That's not what it's about.

07:22.887 --> 07:25.511
If you do choose to join with it, it'll certainly open you up.

07:26.492 --> 07:33.402
You know, God can speak to you and show you things in your life that maybe you have missed, but you don't do it to win God's favor.

07:35.285 --> 07:38.650
You know, God's love is not dependent upon how you act.

07:39.771 --> 07:40.452
Thank you, Lord.

07:42.175 --> 07:46.962
His love is placed on you because of who you are and not by what you do.

07:47.618 --> 07:52.604
Now, if you do some stupid things, you might have to deal with those consequences, but that does not affect his love towards you.

07:53.365 --> 07:56.289
He places value on you no matter what your actions might be.

07:56.950 --> 08:04.420
And there's nothing you can do other than look at that fact that he will never love you any less or love you anymore based on what you do.

08:05.281 --> 08:09.626
And the reason is because what Jesus did outshines what we do.

08:10.648 --> 08:12.370
Again, thank you, God.

08:13.858 --> 08:20.288
So with that understanding, it's important to know that we're still called though to love God back.

08:20.308 --> 08:22.972
Right, what did Jesus tell us that greatest commandment was?

08:24.294 --> 08:27.559
Love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, with all your mind.

08:28.921 --> 08:34.209
First John 4 tells us that we love because he first loved us.

08:34.289 --> 08:40.999
So see, it's in view of God's love to us that our response should be to love him back.

08:41.019 --> 08:42.962
It should be kind of an automatic response.

08:43.938 --> 08:48.504
You know, it's automatic responses like if someone sneezes, you say, bless you.

08:48.825 --> 08:50.026
It's just automatic.

08:50.046 --> 08:53.030
Or if you're in Green Bay, if someone goes, don't, don't, don't, don't, don't, don't.

08:53.050 --> 08:58.457
Go back, go back.

08:58.478 --> 08:59.579
Something holy about that.

09:01.562 --> 09:02.303
And that's what Lent is.

09:02.363 --> 09:08.291
Lent in seasons like this, it's about us loving God back.

09:08.311 --> 09:13.778
It's not to earn anything, it's simply to acknowledge that He has our attention.

09:15.778 --> 09:19.283
You know, it's not to earn anything, it's just simply to acknowledge him.

09:20.906 --> 09:25.172
And it's when he moves in us that we are then equipped to serve him.

09:25.192 --> 09:27.055
See, we can serve him because of what he did in us.

09:28.216 --> 09:43.058
He was 13, in verse 20, he says, now made the God of peace who through the blood of the eternal covenant brought back from the dead are Lord Jesus, that great shepherd of the sheep, equip you with everything good for doing his will.

09:43.170 --> 09:50.277
And may he work in us what is pleasing to him through Jesus Christ, to whom be glory forever and ever.

09:50.837 --> 09:51.198
Amen.

09:52.919 --> 09:56.883
See, it's in this examining of our souls that we need to ask ourselves, how are we doing with this?

09:58.364 --> 10:01.227
How are we responding to the grace that's been given to us?

10:01.587 --> 10:02.709
How are we responding to him?

10:04.090 --> 10:06.372
Because it's very easy to become a complacent Christian.

10:06.652 --> 10:09.095
Goodness, I know that I'm guilty of that.

10:09.875 --> 10:12.658
I find myself getting basically lazy in God's grace.

10:14.562 --> 10:23.231
You know, but there's a verse as well in 1 Corinthians 15 where Paul says, he said, by the grace of God, I am what I am.

10:23.911 --> 10:27.335
And his grace to me was not without effect.

10:28.336 --> 10:30.718
See, the question is, is God's grace having an effect on you?

10:31.980 --> 10:33.982
And what is that effect?

10:34.002 --> 10:40.568
Because he goes on to say, he says, no, I worked harder than all of them, yet not I, but the grace of God that was given me.

10:40.588 --> 10:42.290
It's the idea of this grace

10:42.818 --> 10:48.806
of God moving in us, moving towards us that equips us back to love Him.

10:51.329 --> 11:08.050
Now, when we get in these times, when we get in these seasons, as we mess with ourselves and we make more time for prayer and stuff, it's kind of saying, how are we doing with our dun dun dun dun dun dun, that automatic response to His grace?

11:11.266 --> 11:12.588
It's so weird having my dad here.

11:15.271 --> 11:16.232
He's hearing his laughter.

11:16.813 --> 11:18.094
He's not here when I speak.

11:18.955 --> 11:20.337
That's something horribly went wrong.

11:20.377 --> 11:20.758
I don't know.

11:20.898 --> 11:21.559
But no.

11:22.299 --> 11:26.204
You know what's funny is yesterday, he just assumed he was talking.

11:26.224 --> 11:28.507
He's like, oh, I guess I got a pair of something for tomorrow.

11:28.527 --> 11:30.029
I was like, what?

11:30.049 --> 11:31.210
No, we planned this a while ago.

11:31.350 --> 11:33.733
Oh, it was like he got a day off.

11:33.893 --> 11:34.254
It was wonderful.

11:34.274 --> 11:37.618
He was excited.

11:38.082 --> 11:41.145
So again, are we allowing that reaction to happen to us?

11:41.165 --> 11:49.855
You know, another text in 2 Corinthians, verse 6, Paul says, as God's co-workers, we urge you not to receive God's grace in vain.

11:50.236 --> 11:52.658
And see, that's what we're doing tonight throughout the season.

11:52.718 --> 11:55.902
We're trying to urge you to not receive God's grace in vain.

11:56.943 --> 12:00.667
So we take times like this to see how we're responding to that grace.

12:01.508 --> 12:04.011
Are we receiving His grace in vain?

12:05.613 --> 12:06.514
And again, I want to

12:07.298 --> 12:09.621
Let you know, I'm not talking about legalism.

12:10.683 --> 12:14.168
This isn't about, well, we have to do this and you have to do that and you better pray this much of it.

12:14.268 --> 12:15.310
That's not what I'm talking about.

12:15.330 --> 12:18.314
This is simply, how are we responding to him?

12:20.197 --> 12:34.738
Titus 2, verse 14 says, Jesus Christ who gave himself for us to redeem us from every lawless deed and to purify for himself a people for his own possession, zealous for good deeds.

12:35.938 --> 12:38.522
And I must be honest, I don't always consider myself a zealous person.

12:38.542 --> 12:41.487
You know, I looked up the definition of zealous, and it's funny, there's two kinds.

12:41.507 --> 12:46.855
There's the very emotional kind, you know, passionate, enthusiastic, energetic.

12:47.396 --> 12:51.302
I don't know that I feel passionate, enthusiastic, and energetic about most things, but that's just my personality.

12:52.504 --> 12:55.569
Then I read the ones that are committed, purposeful, and dedicated.

12:55.629 --> 12:56.991
Well, shoot, I don't get out of zealous.

12:58.032 --> 13:04.242
Those I get, and those I understand, but it's this idea when it moves in you, there should be something in us that has this passion

13:04.642 --> 13:07.967
that we're dedicated to doing these good deeds.

13:09.089 --> 13:10.952
You know, am I purposeful in doing good deeds?

13:11.573 --> 13:12.514
Things that are of God.

13:13.195 --> 13:16.000
Again, we're not talking about doing things to earn anything from God.

13:16.781 --> 13:19.425
In fact, we don't really want what we've earned from God.

13:20.407 --> 13:25.274
But it's this ideal of this zealousness is just that we have tasted grace.

13:26.156 --> 13:30.403
Now we are equipped and we are zealous to bring a change into the world.

13:31.044 --> 13:32.626
And this is the idea of Lent.

13:33.858 --> 13:42.070
that it will mess with us, it will mature us, and we will be able to leave our mark on the planet instead of just a stain.

13:45.855 --> 13:51.544
Now, this idea of land, as we move towards God, it's, you know, you hear us say, of making room for God.

13:51.564 --> 13:57.212
You know, it's this idea of if I was driving, you were going to jump in my car and there was a bunch of stuff in my front seat.

13:57.352 --> 13:58.834
I'd have to move that stuff.

13:59.554 --> 14:00.435
to allow you to come in.

14:00.636 --> 14:01.898
That's kind of the idea here.

14:01.918 --> 14:04.061
This is why we do things a little differently.

14:04.081 --> 14:06.685
This is why we might fast something or we take extra time out.

14:07.026 --> 14:11.132
We're sort of making room for God in our life.

14:13.356 --> 14:20.106
It's like in Isaiah 40, where it says, comfort, comfort my people says you're God.

14:20.848 --> 14:27.538
Speak tenderly to Jerusalem and proclaim to her that her hard service has been completed, that her sin has been paid for.

14:27.714 --> 14:30.998
that she has received from the Lord's hand, double for all her sins.

14:32.200 --> 14:40.450
And then it says, as a voice of one calling in the wilderness, prepare the way for the Lord, make straight in the desert a highway for our God.

14:40.470 --> 14:45.336
It's this idea of what are we doing in our lives to make our path straight.

14:45.997 --> 14:51.885
When we look and we see how we're reacting, we might see things that, oh, we're not operating under manufacturer recommendations.

14:52.325 --> 14:53.947
Oh, I got a little upset here.

14:54.047 --> 14:55.109
Man, that's driving me crazy.

14:55.469 --> 14:56.050
I know just,

14:56.578 --> 14:59.801
You know, fasting today, for some reason traffic was just worse today.

15:01.543 --> 15:03.625
And everyone just wanted to test my patience.

15:03.805 --> 15:05.727
It's like everyone forgot how to use blinkers or whatever.

15:05.747 --> 15:09.951
It's like you catch yourself just, you know, you see those little things that manifest inside of you.

15:09.971 --> 15:11.332
It's like, whoa, hold on.

15:12.353 --> 15:15.897
What can I do to make the path straight, make room for God?

15:15.957 --> 15:25.106
Because check this, it says, when we do that in verse four, it says, every valley shall be raised up in every mountain and hill be made low.

15:27.842 --> 15:34.392
You know, if you're sitting right now and you think there's something in your life that seems like it's such a chasm between you and where you want to be.

15:35.653 --> 15:40.200
Such a mountain in front of you from where you are and where you want to be, you can't even see it.

15:41.622 --> 15:42.363
This should bring you hope.

15:43.945 --> 15:50.755
Because it says, when we make the path straight, that he will take those valleys, they shall be raised up in every mountain, be made low.

15:51.737 --> 15:53.279
It says, the rough ground shall become level.

15:53.720 --> 15:55.282
The rugged places are plain.

15:56.034 --> 16:00.259
And it says this, and then the glory of the Lord will be revealed.

16:01.740 --> 16:02.741
And all people will see it.

16:03.963 --> 16:06.786
When God moves in your life, you notice it.

16:07.326 --> 16:07.907
You feel it.

16:08.307 --> 16:09.629
It's so real.

16:10.690 --> 16:11.611
And that's what we're looking for.

16:11.631 --> 16:13.153
And that's what our hope is through this season.

16:13.213 --> 16:21.682
And as we go through and we make room for God, as you take more time and find more time for prayer, pull something out of your life just to mess with yourself.

16:23.394 --> 16:28.926
that we're doing that to make a pass straight for God because we need Him in our lives and we want His glory revealed in our lives.

16:28.986 --> 16:29.287
Amen.

16:30.830 --> 16:31.732
All right, well, let's do this.

16:31.772 --> 16:36.101
Let me close in prayer and I'll pray for the food and then we can head on out.

16:36.242 --> 16:42.034
Now, I need to tell you, there are some rules that gave me about picking up your children.

16:42.850 --> 16:49.479
And then I was joking with Becky, and now I'm trying to remember if I remember the actual ones, or if I just remember the jokes that I made out of what she told me.

16:50.079 --> 16:50.600
So we'll see.

16:52.543 --> 16:53.183
We'll see if I give it.

16:53.404 --> 17:04.218
If I understand correctly, if you have a child up through grade school, so sixth grader lower, fourth grader lower.

17:04.578 --> 17:10.706
When we dismiss, you can go and get those children right away, and then you can come back and eat.

17:10.850 --> 17:18.338
However, if your child is above said age group, you can wait until 8 p.m. to pick them up.

17:19.439 --> 17:20.741
All right, let's close in prayer.

17:20.821 --> 17:23.784
God, we thank you for your grace.

17:24.224 --> 17:28.909
And Lord, we do ask for your glory to be revealed in every person here as we join together.

17:28.950 --> 17:39.060
And Lord, we know we don't do this out of some compulsory thing of this somehow gets us closer to you or we climb another rung in our Christian level.

17:39.741 --> 17:40.562
But we do this

17:40.706 --> 17:44.232
through view of your grace of what you've done for us.

17:45.373 --> 17:47.096
And Lord, we thank you for what you've done for us.

17:48.679 --> 17:52.645
And Lord, I pray as well just for this time as we get the head out and hang.

17:52.725 --> 17:56.891
